\f0\fs18 Returning inside he set four more watches, himself taking the middle watch with Kerbol.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 One problem temporarily shoved back out of the way.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Tick, the hatchet-faced pilot, was engaged in conversation with Chevrr, his brittle countryman. Barch joined them. "How did you get your assignments? Did you work out of a central transportation depot?" he asked.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Correct. My depot is\emdash was\emdash Quodaras Thirteen, and every day I might receive a different assignment."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "You must know Magarak well."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 Tick preened himself. "As well as any man can know it."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi125\sl-206\slmult0\f0\fs18 "What if there was freight for a strange location?"\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "There is always the locator in the dome."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 "Locator?" Barch pricked up his ears. "A chart?"\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 Tick said with airy superiority, as if he himself had designed the mechanism, "No, no. Much more complicated and complete. It's a three-dimensional view-box, indexed to all parts of Magarak."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Let's look at this locator."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Tick spoke volubly as they climbed the winding passage to Big Hole. "... a good barge, a fine sleek barge, freshly fueled, and why? Because I, Tick, have done favors for Goleimpas Gstad, dispatcher for Quodaras Thirteen: a Bornghaleze, very influential. 'Tick,' says Gstad, 'the range of the hangar is yours; select a barge which reflects your own excellence.' So daily I watch the route strip and only two days past comes a barge fresh from the growth vats\emdash "\f1\fs24\par
