\scaps\f0\fs18 Gray \scaps0 daylight poured past the catwalk into the hold. Barch heard the hiss of rain. A moment passed. Then the barge rose, headed out into the rain. The little round men slid behind the sustenators. The Podruods spat and blew.\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 Looking up into the stormy sky, Barch glimpsed the black shuttle of traffic. The struts pressed hard into his aching bones as the raft slid up on a slant. Barch eased his gun into position; he saw Kerbol follow suit.\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 They were flying in the stream of traffic. Barch could see nameless faces, pale splotches, peering blankly out into the rain. He should have instructed Tick to steer free of the lanes.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 The barge slid along at a steady pace. With a maddening sense of momentum and direction, Barch realized that Tick would obey him literally, fly to Gdoa. Rain slanted across the barge like strings of gray wool. Barch could see water trickling down the red skin of the Podruods. The spikes of black hair drooped, fell like seaweed over the bull-shoulders.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 The raft above slid sharply away. Barch squinted up into the sodden sky. So far as he could see\emdash clear. He pushed the gun into the hold. "Wait!" muttered Kerbol.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 A crystal-domed raft came darting overhead, hesitated like a hummingbird at a flower. Barch saw the maroon of Bornghalese skin. He glanced anxiously back to the Podruods; Kerbol's voice had sounded loud in his ears\emdash but no, the hissing rain would drown out sound. The Bornghalese raft darted away.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch leveled the gun, glanced at Kerbol. Kerbol nodded. Barch pressed the trigger button. The Podruods dropped, one toppled over the side. Barch slipped down into the hold, stood bent nearly double from cramp and bone-ache. He hobbled out into the rain, looked up.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 A Podruod loomed over him like a tower, but his gaze was toward the stern. Attracted by Barch's movement he looked down, opened his cavernous mouth. Barch fired. The body toppled at him like a falling statue. Barch ducked back, the body crumpled on the deck.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch swung to observe the little round men. They stood like a row of pumpkins, little round eyes staring.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch climbed cautiously up on the catwalk. Kerbol was there already. He ran astern, took the Podruod serpent lashes. He peered over the side; the gigantic welter of Magarak pulsed, whirled, shuttled, gleamed. Barch decided against dumping the corpses: somewhere was the coordinator, the Magarak brain, fitting incoming data into patterns. Instead he slid the corpses into the hold, ran forward to the pilot dome. Tick was singing to himself in a peculiar falsetto whine, and at first paid Barch no head.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch rapped at the back of the narrow head. "Wake up."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Tick gave him a sad glance.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch went to the locator, reached under, snapped the chain as he had seen Tick do. "Now, how do you turn off the pointer light?"\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Push back the slide, break the bulb."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch did so. "Take us up into the clouds and head for home."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 He went back aft, stood looking critically into the hold. The little fat men eyed him nervously. Barch growled under his breath. What to do with them? There was nothing he could do, except take them back to the cave.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 He jumped down into the hold. "My name is Barch."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 They looked at him solemnly. Barch said brusquely, "You're free men now; you're slaves no longer."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 The little man closest to him asked anxiously, "How is this possible?"\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "You have heard of the mountain where the wild men hide? That's where you're going now."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 The little fat man shuffled nervously. "But why have you gone to such lengths for our benefit?"\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\b\scaps\f0\fs18 "I \b0\scaps0 haven't. \b\scaps I \b0\scaps0 wanted a few of those sustenators. The only way \b\scaps I \b0\scaps0 could get them was to steal the cargo. You happened to be aboard."\f1\fs24\par
