\f0\fs18 He went on. There was the very spot on which Claude Darran's body had lain. And there\emdash he looked up. Approaching was a young Lekthwan, gold skin splendid in the sunlight. He wore black trousers, a soft black cloak and cap. Many times Barch had seen Markel in the same garb; it gave him a curious pang of timelessness.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 The Lekthwan halted in front of Barch. "Why are you here?" he asked courteously.\f1\fs24\par
