\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 "By a very simple means. Perhaps it may strike you as primitive. After we left Magarak we searched the sky. In one direction, in only one direction could we expect to find familiar constellations: in the direction diametrically across the sun from Magarak. We found Orion, very small, very faint. We started in that direction, and kept on going."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "That was very ingenious. I was sure you would get home."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\sl-208\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 Barch smiled grimly. "I was never quite so sure."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 She looked out into the warm air, hazy with afternoon vapor. "I feel I must explain to you\emdash "\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 "Forget it," said Barch. "I know all about it. It wasn't your idea. The Lenape said, The crazy man is gone; now is a good time, we'll escape him and his mad ideas as well as the Klau,' and everybody thought it was a good idea."\f1\fs24\par
