\pard\fi288\qj\f0\fs18 He returned to the terrace. Komeitk Lelianr still stood leaning back with her elbows on the balustrade. She was looking at him; she radiated an attraction, a physical force that impelled him toward her. He took a short step forward, halted. She looked at him with \fs16 a \fs18 curious expression neither inviting nor forbidding. Barch took \fs16 a \fs18 deep breath.\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 "Good-by, Ellen."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 "Good-by, Roy."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 He ran to the helicopter, jumped in. The pilot was reading \fs16 a \fs18 magazine.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Let's go," said Barch.\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\qj\f0\fs18 The pilot stretched languidly. "Finish so soon?"\f1\fs24\par
\pard\f0\fs18 "Finish?" muttered Barch. "What do you mean 'finish?' There's nothing in life that has a finish."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "You're beyond me there, mister."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Let's go," said Barch shortly.\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 The pilot looked down the terrace. "That young lady is coming down this way."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 Barch slowly stepped out of the cab. He saw that she was breathing very hard. Her mouth was firm, pale, tight.\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Well?"\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\qj\f0\fs18 "I don't want you to leave."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\f0\fs18 "But-"\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi288\sl240\slmult1\qj\f0\fs18 "Roy\emdash it's taking a chance. I'm willing if you are."\f1\fs24\par
\pard\fi192\sl-245\slmult0\qj\f0\fs18 He made no pretense of misunderstanding. "A big chance. You'll be cut off from your people."\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 "Perhaps, perhaps not.... Are you afraid?"\f1\fs24\par
\f0\fs18 Barch looked at her long seconds. Something warm broke inside him. "No. I'm not afraid."\f1\fs24\par
